The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Three killed in road mishaps
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Three killed in road mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Three people were killed and five seriously injured in a series of accidents in the city on Tuesday night and Wednesday.         
	Two of the deceased were motorcycle-borne youths speeding down the AJC Bose Road flyover without helmets. Police said the mishap occurred when the duo were racing another bike-borne youth towards the Maidan end of the flyover.         
	They were heading towards Mominpur from Park Circus and were racing dangerously. The driver of one of the motorcycles  Sheikh Sahnawaz, 22  crashed into a Matador plying in the same direction, said Jawed Shamim, the joint commissioner of police (headquarters).        
	Pillion rider Sohrab Alam, 22, died on the spot from head injuries while Sahnawaz was admitted to SSKM Hospital by the police. Sahnawaz succumbed to his injuries early on Wednesday. Both were residents of Mominpur.        
	The rider of the other motorcycle, Mohammad Rizwan, 22, lost control of his vehicle and fell down on seeing his friend ram into the Matador and sustained serious head and chest injuries. He was also admitted to SSKM Hospital.         
	On Wednesday morning, Mihir Kamdar, 25, was mowed down by an army truck on Syed Amir Ali Avenue. According to an officer of Karaya police station, the truck knocked down Kamdar while he was crossing the road at 10.45am. Residents rushed him to National Medical College and Hospital, where he died. The truck driver was arrested.        
	Two persons were seriously injured when a truck and a trailer collided at the Hatibagan crossing around midnight on Tuesday. The truck driver, who lost control of his vehicle, and his help were admitted to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, said a traffic cop. Later that night, three persons were injured when a Matador collided with a truck on JL Nehru Road in front of American Center.        
	The Matador entered AJC Bose Road after crossing the southern flank of the Park Street flyover and collided with the truck which was going north. The driver, his help and another occupant of the van were admitted to SSKM Hospital.                                                                                                                                                          
